A family in Kisumu is seeking justice after their nephew was allegedly assaulted by some relatives. Munawar Abdallah, 22, is admitted to Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital in Eldoret. On Monday, two suspects Abdallah Ahmed Said and Abdul Naji Faruk were charged in aÂ Winam court of causing grievous harm to Abdallah on October 6 at Patel's flats along the Kisumu-Kakamega Road. The two pleaded not guilty before resident magistrate Caroline Njalale. They were each released on a Sh100,000 bond, with a surety of the same amount. The prosecution told the court the complainant is still in critical condition.  Munawar Abdallah's stitched head after the attack. /FAITH MATETE The magistrate ordered the suspects to report to Kondele police station every Wednesday until investigations are completed. Relative Munirah Khadija earlier said her nephew was attacked when he visited his uncle. Khadija told the press they first took Munawar to Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Hospital before he was moved to Eldoret. The family appealed to the Director of Public Prosecutions to ensure their nephew gets justice. The matter will be mentioned on October 29 and the hearing is scheduled for November 19. Click here for the latest political news 